---
/**
 * storage-engines · storage-engines-fundamentals · Figure 9 — Level 9, an OLTP
 * point lookup on a row store versus an OLAP scan on a column store.
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from the source page (figure + svg + figcaption), including
 * the rotated <text transform="rotate(...)"> column labels. This figure
 * references no markers, so it needs no local <defs>.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 560 150"
        role="img"
        aria-label="OLTP point lookup on a row store versus OLAP scan on a column store"
    >
        <g font-family="ui-sans-serif,system-ui,sans-serif">
            <text
                x="140"
                y="18"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#1f3a5a">OLTP → ROW store</text
            >
            <text
                x="420"
                y="18"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#2f5d3a">OLAP → COLUMN store</text
            >
            <rect x="40" y="34" width="200" height="26" rx="5" fill="#f1eee2" stroke="#1f3a5a"
            ></rect><text x="140" y="51" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5"
                >[id|region|status|ts|qty|amount]</text
            >
            <text x="140" y="80" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#2f5d3a"
                >1 seek → whole record</text
            >
            <text x="140" y="96" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#9a2417"
                >but a column scan drags every column</text
            >
            <line x1="280" y1="10" x2="280" y2="140" stroke="#d8d4c8" stroke-dasharray="4 4"></line>
            <g font-size="8.5">
                <rect x="316" y="32" width="34" height="74" rx="4" fill="#fff" stroke="#d8d4c8"
                ></rect><text x="333" y="72" text-anchor="middle" transform="rotate(-90 333 72)"
                    >id</text
                >
                <rect x="354" y="32" width="34" height="74" rx="4" fill="#eef5ee" stroke="#2f5d3a"
                ></rect><text
                    x="371"
                    y="72"
                    text-anchor="middle"
                    transform="rotate(-90 371 72)"
                    fill="#244a2e">region</text
                >
                <rect x="392" y="32" width="34" height="74" rx="4" fill="#fff" stroke="#d8d4c8"
                ></rect><text x="409" y="72" text-anchor="middle" transform="rotate(-90 409 72)"
                    >status</text
                >
                <rect x="430" y="32" width="34" height="74" rx="4" fill="#fff" stroke="#d8d4c8"
                ></rect><text x="447" y="72" text-anchor="middle" transform="rotate(-90 447 72)"
                    >ts</text
                >
                <rect x="468" y="32" width="34" height="74" rx="4" fill="#fff" stroke="#d8d4c8"
                ></rect><text x="485" y="72" text-anchor="middle" transform="rotate(-90 485 72)"
                    >qty</text
                >
                <rect x="506" y="32" width="34" height="74" rx="4" fill="#eef5ee" stroke="#2f5d3a"
                ></rect><text
                    x="523"
                    y="72"
                    text-anchor="middle"
                    transform="rotate(-90 523 72)"
                    fill="#244a2e">amount</text
                >
            </g>
            <text x="428" y="124" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#2f5d3a"
                >SUM(amount) BY region → read 2 blocks, skip 4</text
            >
            <text x="428" y="140" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f"
                >same-domain values compress hard (RLE, dictionary)</text
            >
        </g>
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        Two compounding wins for columnar: read only the columns named, and compress same-domain
        runs hard. The <em>i</em>-th value in every column file is the same row.
    </figcaption>
</figure>
